Pascal is an influential computer programming language named after the mathematician [[Wikipedia:Blaise Pascal|Blaise Pascal]].  It was invented by [[Wikipedia:Niklaus Wirth|Niklaus Wirth]] in 1968 as a research project into the nascent field of compiler theory.

